## Spec Organization

Specs are organized into **platform specs** (shared across subsystems) and **subsystem specs** (specific to one vertical/module). See `docs/spec-strategy.md` for the methodology.

```
docs/
├── spec-strategy.md              # Methodology for all specs
├── spec/                         # Platform-level shared specs
│   ├── index.md                  # Start here - overview + links to subsystems
│   ├── stack.md                  # Shared tech stack
│   ├── backend.md                # Shared backend architecture
│   ├── ui.md                     # Shared design system
│   ├── templates/                # Templates for bootstrapping new subsystems
│   └── archive/                  # Historical specs kept for reference
│
├── {{subsystem}}/spec/           # Subsystem specs
│   ├── index.md                  # Subsystem overview + related platform specs
│   ├── build-order.md            # Subsystem-specific build order
│   └── [feature].md              # Feature specs
│
└── {{another-subsystem}}/spec/
    └── ...
```

**When working on a feature:**
1. Read the subsystem's feature spec (e.g., `docs/{{subsystem}}/spec/feature-name.md`)
2. Check the "Related Specs" table at the top - it points to shared platform specs
3. Consult platform specs (`stack.md`, `backend.md`, `ui.md`) for infrastructure, patterns, and conventions

**Spec status:**
- ✅ Complete - Spec is written and approved
- 🔲 Pending - Placeholder with structure, needs content

